tldr: The user wanted a complete aesthetic refresh for their sleep questionnaire
  app. I implemented a new calming, sleep-themed design, fixed a console error
  related to input values, and am now addressing further color inconsistencies
  in the report section based on user feedback.
overview: "The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetics
  of their sleep questionnaire app, moving it from a generic look to a more
  polished and calming sleep-themed design. The approach involved a multi-step
  process: first, a new color palette was defined and applied globally. Then,
  core UI components like cards, checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and
  progress bars were enhanced. The main questionnaire form and the introductory
  section were redesigned with thematic elements and improved visual hierarchy.
  All individual questionnaire sections were updated to ensure consistent
  styling for form field groupings. During this process, a console error related
  to  values being passed to input fields was identified and resolved.
  Finally, based on user feedback and a provided screenshot, it was noted that
  the Report section's card headers still contained hardcoded, inconsistent
  gradient colors, which will be addressed in the next iteration to achieve full
  aesthetic consistency."
